-------------------------------------------------------
Encore: Driver generator script

drvencore 25th Jan 2011 BE/CO/HT Julian.Lewis@cern.ch
-------------------------------------------------------

No Parameters:
   To print this help text from drvencore type
      drvencore

Parameter One: <driver name>
   To run drvencore to build the rf_vtu driver from Oracle
      drvencore rf_vtu

Parameter Two: <cpu type>
   The default for CPU is set L865
   it can be overridden
      drvencore rf_vtu L865_64

Parameter Three: <kernel version>
   The default for the Kernel version is set 2.6.24.7-rt27
   it can be overridden
      drvencore rf_vtu L865 2.6.24.7-rt27

Parameter Four: <registers file>
   To run drvencore to build the cvora driver from a hand made regs
   file specify the name of a local register file (It can have any name)
      drvencore cvora L865 2.6.24.7-rt27 CVORA.regs

Thus the command parameters for drvencore are as follows:

   drvencore [<driver name>] [<cpu type> [<kernel version> [<registers file>]]]

-----------------------------------------------------
Encore: Driver, libraries, includes and
testprogram installer

insencore 27th Jan 2011 BE/CO/HT Julian.Lewis@cern.ch
-----------------------------------------------------

No Parameters:
   To print this help text from insencore type
      insencore

Parameter One: <driver name>
   To run insencore to install the rf_vtu driver
      insencore rf_vtu

Parameter Two: <cpu type>
   The default for CPU is set L865
   it can be overridden
      insencore rf_vtu L865_64

Parameter Three: <kernel version>
   The default for the Kernel version is set 2.6.24.7-rt27
   it can be overridden
      insencore rf_vtu L865 2.6.24.7-rt27

Parameter Four: <accelerator complex>
   The default accelerator complex is lab
      insencore cvora L865 2.6.24.7-rt27 operlhc

Thus the command parameters for insencore are as follows:

   insencore [<driver name>] [<cpu type> [<kernel version> [<accelerator complex>]]]

Julian
